
What it is: Managing time synchronization on a Linux system. Crucial for servers, logs, and security.

Key Concepts to Learn:

NTP (Network Time Protocol): The protocol used to sync time.

timedatectl: The modern command to control the system time and time synchronization.

Commands:

timedatectl status: Check the current time and status of time sync.

sudo timedatectl set-ntp true: Enable automatic time sync via NTP.
